						<div class="postbody">I always wondered that as well. I know the DS' sound channels have an option to generate square waves or white noise without requiring samples, but my understanding is that this mode is sparsely used by DS games. I don't know whether this was used to support GB(C)'s sound backwards compatibility or not. In all cases, compatibility seems complete and I've yet to see games which sounds any different on a DS than on a GBA (the same cannot be said about GBA emulators...) I could be wrong, though.</div>

