				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Supposedly, the DS mixes sound at 1,048,576Hz 24-bit, then cuts that down to 32768Hz 10-bit with PWM.  But I've found that PSG sounds really bad on the DS, it sounds very aliased.  So you'd get better sound with a software mixer that synthesizes sound at 32768Hz.<br />If it's mixing 16 channels at ~1MHz, it's probably playing all 16 sound channels in series for left and right channels, then downsampling with PWM.  It wouldn't be playing PSG sound at anything faster than 32768Hz.<br /><br />There is a GBA sound chip in there too, but it's completely inaccessible in DS mode.<br /><br />I bet they kept PSG sound in there (DS MODE) just for the Pokemon cries.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Here come the fortune cookies!  Here come the fortune cookies!  They're wearing paper hats!</div>
					
