						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I bet they kept PSG sound in there just for the Pokemon cries.</div><br />That plus Nintendo knew how much CPU and programmer time was associated with software mixing. Some games (such as <em>Doom</em> and <em>Pinobee</em>) use the GBC channels for music and the GBA channels for PCM sound streamed directly from ROM rather than mixed in RAM, and even games with a software mixer (such as <em>Mario Kart Super Circuit</em>) run some instruments on the PSG.</div>

