				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">On a GBA you can request a PWM update rate of 131,072Hz with 7-bit audio, or even 262,144Hz with 6-bit audio.  You can't do that on a DS.<br />I guess someone could try to figure out the quantization noise you'd get with aliased sampling at 131072Hz, but it's a lot less than the artifacts you'd get at 32768Hz.</div>

					
